article.headline: Thomas' 22 lead Hofstra over Delaware 76-71
article.description: — Tyler Thomas scored 22 points as Hofstra beat Delaware 76-71 on Saturday.
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- — Tyler Thomas scored 22 points as Hofstra beat Delaware 76-71 on Saturday. Thomas added six rebounds and three blocks for the Pride (8-7, 1-1 Coastal Athletic Association). Darlinstone Dubar added 18 points and Jacco Fritz was 6 of 6 scored 15. Christian Ray led the way for the Fightin' Blue Hens (9-6, 1-1) with 20 points, 10 rebounds and two steals. Jyare Davis added 11 points and five assists for Delaware. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
